article.description: Southern Miss tops North Texas in overtime 75-71
article.headline: Southern Miss tops North Texas in overtime 75-71
article.linkText: Southern Miss tops North Texas in overtime 75-71
article.story: DENTON, Texas -- Chip Armelin scored a career-high 30, including a key 3-pointer in overtime, to lift Southern Miss over North Texas 75-71 on Saturday. Jordan Williams made 1 of 2 from the line to put North Texas up one with 1:50 left in overtime, but Southern Miss (6-12, 1-6 Conference USA) scored the next six points -- including Armelin's trey -- for the win. Armelin was 10 of 17 from the floor, including 4 of 9 beyond the arc. Norville Carey added 18 points and 12 boards. North Texas (8-11, 2-5) took advantage of two 3-pointers by Maurice Aniefiok late in the first to lead 37-29 at the break. Southern Miss came back and finally tied it at 55 with 4:02 left on Matt Bingaya's three-point play. Carey's 3-pointer with four seconds left forced overtime. Williams led North Texas with 19 points. Jeremy Combs had 17 points and nine boards and Aniefiok finished with 16.
